                <li>
                  <b>Washer Not Draining</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>When your washer isn’t draining, our technicians check the <strong>drain pump</strong> and <strong>hoses</strong> for blockages. We use our professional tools to clear out any debris clogging the system. If the <strong>water pump</strong> is faulty, we replace it to ensure proper drainage. We also check the <strong>control board</strong> to ensure it sends the correct signals for draining. Your washer will drain properly once the blockage or mechanical issue is fixed.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Washer Won't Spin</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>Our team first checks the drive belt and motor for washers that won't spin. If the belt is worn out, we replace it with a new one. We also check the <strong>lid switch</strong> and replace it if it works incorrectly. If the issue is due to an imbalance, we adjust the load or check the <strong>suspension system</strong> to balance it out and allow it to spin correctly. Your washer will then complete its cycles as intended.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Washer Leaking Water</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>Our technicians find the source of the leak by checking the <strong>door seal</strong>, <strong>hoses</strong>, and <strong>water pump</strong>. If the <strong>door seal</strong> is damaged, we replace it to prevent future leaks. We repair or replace any faulty hoses and ensure the <strong>washer drum</strong> is intact. If the leak is due to improper installation, we reconfigure the setup to prevent further water damage.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Washer is Loud or Vibrating</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>When your washer makes strange noises or vibrates too much, our team checks the <strong>drum bearings</strong>, <strong>suspension system</strong>, and <strong>shock absorbers</strong>. We replace worn-out bearings to reduce noise and make it run smoothly. If the <strong>suspension system</strong> is compromised, we make the necessary adjustments or replacements to stop the vibration. This will make your washer quiet and efficient again.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Washer Won’t Fill with Water</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>If your washer isn’t filling with water, our technicians check the <strong>water inlet valve</strong> and <strong>electronic sensors</strong> that control the water levels. We test the valve for any blockages and replace it if necessary. We also check the <strong>control board</strong> to ensure it sends the correct signals to fill the washer properly. Once the issue is fixed, your machine will fill with the right amount of water for each cycle.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Washer Door Won’t Lock or Unlock</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>A faulty <strong>door lock assembly</strong> will prevent your washer from starting or finishing a cycle. Our technicians first check the <strong>door lock mechanism</strong> and replace any faulty parts. We also check the <strong>control board</strong> to ensure it communicates with the door lock correctly. Once the repair is done, the door will lock and unlock as it should, and the washer will work properly.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Washer Stuck in Cycle or Not Finishing Cycles</b>
                  <p style="text-align: start"><strong>How We Fix It:</strong><br>Our team checks the control board and timer for faults when a washer is stuck in a cycle or not finishing a cycle. We troubleshoot the electronic components and replace any faulty parts so the washer can advance through its cycles. If the issue is with the <strong>door lock</strong>, we repair or replace the lock mechanism so the cycle will finish as expected.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
